Rating: 4
You have to try these. They are wonderful! If you are looking for something really different, this is it. I think it is a fun snack for kids to make.

Rating: 3
This was putzy to make but so interesting and fun. I served it on red cabbage leaves and it looked beautiful. Guests were intrigued and kept going back for more. It was actually fun to make and so different it was a conversation starter. We had this with a peach/cream cheese/carribbean spice spread with dainty light crackers and champagne. Wonderful combination.

Rating: 2
This is very strange tasting. I made them and they were eaten quickly but people couldn't decide if they were delicious or disgusting. The reason they were gone so quick is curiosity. Nice idea though.

Rating: 3
I made this for a ladies luncheon and everyone raved about it. They were usually surprised to find a grape in the center. I assembled the grapes on leaves to resemble a bunch of grapes.

Rating: 4
Great! Took these to an office snack-potluck today & almost had to police the table to keep folks from taking a plate full! Labor-intensive, but terrific.

Rating: 3
I've served these at two different parties--a birthday and a holiday party. They're so unusual and attractive and light that they're always a stand out. People are amazed when they learn what they are.

Rating: 4
Oh My Gosh!! This recipe was the best!! The flavor is wonderful and the varieties of texture is such a delight!! The roasted pecans add a crunch, the cream cheese is of course creamy and the grape is the sweet surprise in the middle!! I made this for a party and did not tell anyone what was in the middle!! My guests loved it!! It is incredibly easy to make and healthy too!!

